  "text": "For graph-structured data, graph kernels for labeled graphs have been proposed [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Since subgraph-based graph kernels are still prohibitively expensive, paths generated by random walks were used as features. A recursive formulation similar to those of the other dynamic programming-based kernels results in a system of linear equations, and allows us to efficiently compute the graph kernels. Several approaches to accelerating the computation are discussed in [CITATION_3] .",
